    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-06T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-06T23:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/17a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-07T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 7, 1943—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1442. With reference to your conversation with Chiang<note n="5" xml:id="d732fn5"
                        >Generalissimo Chiang Kai-shek, President of the Chinese Executive Yuan
                        (Premier); he was inaugurated as President of the Chinese National
                        Government on October 10, 1943.</note> (Embassy’s 1871)<note n="6"
                        xml:id="d732fn6">Telegram No. 1871, October 6, 11 a.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_872">p. 872</ref>.</note> the Department would appreciate
                    receiving by radio a detailed account of his questions and comments in regard to
                    Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
